      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:3:2:21:28",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/11/28",
      "text": [
        " \"لاَ بَأْسَ بِذَلِكَ وَ لَكِنْ لاَ يَبِيعُهُمْ مُرَابَحَةً \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3799 - Abu al-Sabbah al-Kinani and Sama'ah narrated from Abu Abdullah (as):\nImam (as) was asked about a man who carries goods for the people of the market, and they have set a price for him. They then say to him, \"Sell it, and whatever profit you make above the price is yours.\"\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in that, but he should not sell it to them as a murabaha (profit-sharing agreement).\""
        ]
      }
    },
